        <h2 class="subheading">Aarogya Aasara</h2>
        <p class="text-justify">In order to achieve "Universal Health Coverage" in the A.P. State through Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust, Government of A.P. has contemplated certain proposals that are to be implemented under Dr.YSR Aarogyasri scheme. </p>
        <p>The AP Government had issued G.O.Rt.No.550, Dt.26.10.2019, HM &amp; FW Dept., permitting the CEO, Dr. YSR AHCT for sanction of "Post-operative sustenance allowance" to the patients who undergo surgeries under Dr. YSR Aarogyasri scheme to compensate the loss of wages @ Rs.225/- per day subject to a maximum of Rs.5000/- per month as prescribed by the experts, before discharge from the hospital. Under this scheme, Dr. YSR AHCT has identified 1,519 procedures in 27 specialties eligible for Post-op sustenance allowance. </p>
        <p>Vide G.O. Rt. No.424, HM &amp; FW (I.1) Dept., dated: 29.09.2020 Govt. Of A.P. have enhanced the postoperative sustenance allowance to all the pregnant women who undergo treatment in Dr. YSR Aarogyasri empanelment network hospitals i.e., Rs.5,000/- to normal deliveries and Rs.3,000/- to caesarean section deliveries in convergence with Janani Suraksha Yojana (JSY) payments. Vide GO Rt No.635, HM &amp; FW (I.1) Dept., dated: 29.07.2022, sustenance allowance to the caesarean section deliveries increased to Rs 5000/-.</p>
